================================================================================
POKÉMARKET DATABASE REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

CURRENT STATUS:
---------------
✅ 2 tables already exist (User, RefreshToken)
❌ 7 tables MISSING and REQUIRED

This document lists ALL database tables needed for the PokéMarket application.
Each table is 100% REQUIRED.


================================================================================
TABLE 1: users (✅ ALREADY EXISTS)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Stores user accounts for authentication
- Tracks seller ratings and transaction history
- Required for login/register functionality
- Every listing, bid, message, and review references a user

SCHEMA:
-------
id              UUID (Primary Key)
username        VARCHAR(30) (Unique, Not Null)
email           VARCHAR(255) (Unique, Not Null)
passwordHash    VARCHAR(255) (Not Null)
avatar          TEXT (URL to profile picture)
bio             TEXT (User description)
verified        BOOLEAN (Default: false) - Shows verified badge
rating          FLOAT (Default: 0) - Average seller rating
totalReviews    INTEGER (Default: 0) - Count of reviews received
totalSales      INTEGER (Default: 0) - Count of completed sales
joinedDate      VARCHAR(50) - Date user registered
createdAt       TIMESTAMP (Default: now())
updatedAt       TIMESTAMP (Auto-update on change)

INDEXES:
- email (for login lookups)
- username (for profile pages)


================================================================================
TABLE 2: refresh_tokens (✅ ALREADY EXISTS)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Implements secure JWT token rotation for authentication
- Prevents security vulnerabilities from stolen tokens
- Each refresh token is single-use and expires after 7 days
- Required for "stay logged in" functionality

SCHEMA:
-------
id          UUID (Primary Key)
tokenHash   VARCHAR(255) (SHA-256 hash of the actual token)
userId      UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
expiresAt   TIMESTAMP (Not Null)
createdAt   TIMESTAMP (Default: now())

INDEXES:
- userId (to find all tokens for a user)
- tokenHash (for fast token validation)


================================================================================
TABLE 3: listings (❌ MISSING - CRITICAL!)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- THE CORE TABLE OF THE ENTIRE APPLICATION
- Without this, there are NO cards to buy, sell, trade, or auction
- Used on: Home page, Search page, Profile page, Dashboard, Detail page
- Every feature in the app depends on listings existing
- Currently using mock data - app cannot function in production without this

SCHEMA:
-------
id                  UUID (Primary Key)
sellerId            UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
title               VARCHAR(200) (Not Null) - Display name like "Charizard Base Set PSA 10"
cardName            VARCHAR(100) (Not Null) - Card name e.g. "Charizard"
set                 VARCHAR(100) - Pokemon set e.g. "Base Set", "Jungle"
cardNumber          VARCHAR(50) - Card number in set e.g. "4/102"
edition             VARCHAR(100) - "1st Edition", "Shadowless", etc.
language            VARCHAR(50) - "English", "Japanese", etc.
condition           VARCHAR(50) - "PSA 10", "PSA 9", "Ungraded", etc.
rarity              VARCHAR(50) - "Common", "Rare Holo", "Secret Rare", etc.
pokemonType         VARCHAR(50) - "Fire", "Water", "Grass", etc.
year                INTEGER - Year card was released
description         TEXT - Detailed description from seller
images              TEXT[] (Array) - URLs to card photos

listingType         VARCHAR(20) (Not Null) - "sale", "trade", or "auction"
price               FLOAT (Nullable) - Fixed price for sale listings
tradePreferences    TEXT (Nullable) - What seller wants to trade for
startingBid         FLOAT (Nullable) - Starting bid for auctions
currentBid          FLOAT (Nullable) - Current highest bid
reservePrice        FLOAT (Nullable) - Minimum acceptable bid
buyItNowPrice       FLOAT (Nullable) - Instant purchase price for auctions
auctionEnd          TIMESTAMP (Nullable) - When auction ends
bidCount            INTEGER (Default: 0) - Number of bids placed

quantity            INTEGER (Default: 1) - How many available
views               INTEGER (Default: 0) - View count for analytics
watchers            INTEGER (Default: 0) - Users who favorited this
status              VARCHAR(20) (Default: 'active') - 'active', 'sold', 'ended', 'traded'

createdAt           TIMESTAMP (Default: now())
updatedAt           TIMESTAMP (Auto-update)

INDEXES:
- sellerId (to find all listings by a user)
- listingType (to filter by sale/trade/auction)
- status (to show only active listings)
- pokemonType (for filtering by type)
- rarity (for filtering by rarity)
- createdAt (for sorting by newest)

USED IN:
- Home.tsx - Featured listings carousel
- Search.tsx - Search and filter cards
- Profile.tsx - User's active listings
- Dashboard.tsx - Seller's dashboard
- ListingDetail.tsx - Individual card details
- ListingCard.tsx - Card display component


================================================================================
TABLE 4: bids (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR AUCTIONS)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Required for auction functionality
- Tracks all bids placed on auction listings
- Shows bid history and current highest bidder
- Used to calculate currentBid and bidCount on listings
- Without this, auctions cannot exist

SCHEMA:
-------
id          UUID (Primary Key)
listingId   UUID (Foreign Key → listings.id, CASCADE DELETE)
userId      UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
amount      FLOAT (Not Null) - Bid amount in dollars
createdAt   TIMESTAMP (Default: now()) - When bid was placed

INDEXES:
- listingId (to get all bids for a listing)
- userId (to get all bids by a user)
- createdAt (to sort bids chronologically)

USED IN:
- ListingDetail.tsx - Shows bid history
- Dashboard.tsx - "My Auctions" tab shows bids received
- Auction countdown displays bidCount


================================================================================
TABLE 5: conversations (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR MESSAGING)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Required for buyer-seller communication
- Creates message threads between two users
- Links conversations to specific listings being discussed
- Without this, users cannot communicate

SCHEMA:
-------
id              UUID (Primary Key)
user1Id         UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
user2Id         UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
listingId       UUID (Foreign Key → listings.id, SET NULL) - Optional link to listing
lastMessageAt   TIMESTAMP (Default: now()) - For sorting conversations
createdAt       TIMESTAMP (Default: now())

UNIQUE CONSTRAINT:
- (user1Id, user2Id, listingId) - Prevents duplicate conversations

INDEXES:
- user1Id (to find user's conversations)
- user2Id (to find user's conversations)
- lastMessageAt (to sort by most recent activity)

USED IN:
- Messages.tsx - Displays conversation list
- Profile.tsx - "Message" button creates conversation
- Navbar.tsx - Shows unread message count


================================================================================
TABLE 6: messages (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR MESSAGING)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Stores actual message content in conversations
- Tracks read/unread status for notifications
- Required for buyer-seller communication about cards
- Without this, messaging system is non-functional

SCHEMA:
-------
id              UUID (Primary Key)
conversationId  UUID (Foreign Key → conversations.id, CASCADE DELETE)
senderId        UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
content         TEXT (Not Null) - Message text
read            BOOLEAN (Default: false) - Read/unread status
createdAt       TIMESTAMP (Default: now())

INDEXES:
- conversationId (to get all messages in a conversation)
- senderId (to identify message author)
- createdAt (to sort messages chronologically)

USED IN:
- Messages.tsx - Displays message history
- Navbar.tsx - Unread count badge
- Real-time chat interface


================================================================================
TABLE 7: reviews (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR RATINGS)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Stores seller ratings and feedback
- Builds trust in the marketplace
- Calculates user.rating and user.totalReviews
- Prevents fraud by showing seller reputation
- Without this, no way to verify seller trustworthiness

SCHEMA:
-------
id          UUID (Primary Key)
reviewerId  UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE) - Who wrote the review
reviewedId  UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE) - Who is being reviewed
listingId   UUID (Foreign Key → listings.id, SET NULL) - Related listing (optional)
rating      INTEGER (Not Null) - 1 to 5 stars
comment     TEXT - Written review
createdAt   TIMESTAMP (Default: now())

INDEXES:
- reviewerId (to find reviews written by a user)
- reviewedId (to find reviews received by a user)
- createdAt (to sort by newest)

USED IN:
- Profile.tsx - "Reviews" tab shows user feedback
- User.rating calculation - Average of all reviews
- User.totalReviews - Count of reviews received
- Seller reputation display


================================================================================
TABLE 8: trade_offers (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR TRADES)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Required for trade listing functionality
- Lets users propose card-for-card trades
- Tracks offer status (pending, accepted, declined)
- Without this, trade listings are non-functional

SCHEMA:
-------
id              UUID (Primary Key)
listingId       UUID (Foreign Key → listings.id, CASCADE DELETE)
fromUserId      UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE) - Who made the offer
offeredCards    TEXT[] (Array) - Names of cards being offered
offeredImages   TEXT[] (Array) - URLs to card images
message         TEXT - Trade proposal message
status          VARCHAR(20) (Default: 'pending') - 'pending', 'accepted', 'declined', 'countered'
createdAt       TIMESTAMP (Default: now())
updatedAt       TIMESTAMP (Auto-update)

INDEXES:
- listingId (to get all offers for a listing)
- fromUserId (to get offers made by a user)
- status (to filter active/pending offers)

USED IN:
- ListingDetail.tsx - Send/receive trade offers
- Dashboard.tsx - "Trades" tab shows offers
- Trade negotiation flow


================================================================================
TABLE 9: watchlist (❌ MISSING - REQUIRED FOR FAVORITES)
================================================================================

WHY WE NEED IT:
- Lets users save/favorite listings
- Tracks listing.watchers count (displayed on cards)
- Creates user's "Favorites" collection
- Users need to track cards they're interested in
- Without this, no way to save listings for later

SCHEMA:
-------
id          UUID (Primary Key)
userId      UUID (Foreign Key → users.id, CASCADE DELETE)
listingId   UUID (Foreign Key → listings.id, CASCADE DELETE)
createdAt   TIMESTAMP (Default: now())

UNIQUE CONSTRAINT:
- (userId, listingId) - User can only favorite a listing once

INDEXES:
- userId (to get user's favorites)
- listingId (to count watchers for a listing)

USED IN:
- ListingDetail.tsx - Heart button to favorite
- Dashboard.tsx - "Favorites" tab
- listing.watchers count display


